variable.name: IDTYPE
variable.description: Framingham Heart Study cohort identifier
variable.comment: IDTYPE and ID taken together form a unique study participant identification number.

variable.name: CD163
variable.description: Scavenger receptor cysteine-rich type 1 protein (M130/CD163) (sample type: plasma)
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for CD163 is 1.65E+03 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 1.18E+06 pg/mL. CD163 values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use CD163_I to see what records are below and above these limits. CD163 values were set to unknown if CD163_CV was greater than or equal to 21.8 for Offspring (IDTYPE = 1) or 24.9 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3).

variable.name: CD163_CV
variable.description: CV for Scavenger receptor cysteine-rich type 1 protein (M130)
variable.comment: CD163 values were set to unknown if CD163_CV was greater than or equal to 21.8 for Offspring (IDTYPE = 1) or 24.9 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3)
